[start section id="20112"]

Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Adams's Service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Lopes, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
At this time I have visited with the White family and informed them that at this time it is unclear as to if adjuvant therapy would be offered in his situation.  Counseled them that it depends on the patient's physical status when he returns, especially due to his past medical history including renal insufficiency, diabetes, and cardiac issues.  Did visit about the two separate malignancies and shared that with just a rectal cancer, one could consider offering chemotherapy.  In regards to the gallbladder cancer, not clear as to if therapy would be offered.  Explained that because only one lymph node was removed unclear as to his risk of recurrence.  Would like the patient to return to have further discussion regarding which avenue would be best to proceed.  At the time of his return I will have him see by Dr. Fredericks, GI Oncology, and Radiation Oncology to determine what are the best treatment options.  Family had numerous questions that I answered to their satisfaction.  They have agreed to return in approximately four weeks' time to have this conversation.  Denies any further questions or concerns.  Has our telephone number to contact us should they have any further questions or concerns.

